  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "We should discourage use of Teku's built-in key generation convenience tools for mainnet deposits. These built-in tools are not [EIP-2333](https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-2333) compatible, do not generate recovery mnemonics, and naively handle the withdrawal keys. In addition, they have not had the required degree of audit scrutiny.\r\n\r\nThe best way to discourage the use of this functionality would be to remove it (or move it to a separate tool if we wished to keep access for some reason).\r\n\r\nWe will recommend to stakers that they use fully audited tools such as the [deposit-cli](https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-deposit-cli) tool that works with Launchpad, or other specialised 3rd-party key management tools.\r\n",
